<subSubSection id="C37713E8AD56FFFC9563FB4C93F3D17A" pageId="14" pageNumber="76" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD24063AD56FFFC9563FB4C93F3D17A" blockId="14.[98,1066,1244,1340]" pageId="14" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD56FFFC9563FB4C92F6D0B7" box="[98,209,1244,1270]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="76">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named after the great entomologist and mentor Dr. José Albertino Rafael, who collected most of the 
<typeStatus id="54D6FEC1AD56FFFC975CFB6F90AAD158" box="[605,653,1279,1305]" pageId="14" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
series and initially “introduced” the neuropterans for the first author.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
