<subSubSection id="C37713E8AD57FFFD956BFAF490ADD230" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD24063AD57FFFD956BFAF490ADD230" blockId="15.[106,1074,1380,1649]" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD956BFAF492E1D13F" box="[106,198,1380,1406]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD57FFFD95D2FAF493AED13F" authority="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb, 2020" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[211,393,1380,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD95D2FAF493AED13F" box="[211,393,1380,1406]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">Purenleon rafaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD948EFAF493E8D13F" bold="true" box="[399,463,1380,1406]" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A210AAD57FFFD948EFAF493E8D13F" box="[399,463,1380,1406]" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is another species fitting in the tibialis species group. It has all the major characters of the group (see remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD57FFFD9612FA1791A5D1E1" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[787,898,1414,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limeirai">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD9612FA1791A5D1E1" box="[787,898,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">P. limeirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), including the female sternite VII with small lobes on the posterior margin. Within the species group, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD57FFFD956BFA5D92EED1A7" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[106,201,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD956BFA5D92EED1A7" box="[106,201,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">P. rafaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD57FFFD9725FA5D9095D1A7" authorityName="Miller &amp; Stange" authorityYear="2014" box="[548,690,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD9725FA5D9095D1A7" box="[548,690,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">P. fernandezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on their general dark body color pattern. Despite the similarities between these two species they can be easily distinguished, since 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD57FFFD9431F98293A8D26A" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[304,399,1553,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD57FFFD9431F98293A8D26A" box="[304,399,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="77">P. rafaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents very unique characteristics within the genus, such as the male parameres (dorsally enlarged and fused, forming a dome) and the female pregenital plate (large with a ventral expansion).
</paragraph>
